  3. Check hourly data upload automation
  4. Validate prediction accuracy on test set

  ---



   How to Start the Servers

  1. Start the Global (Flower) Server

  cd airhub-ml
  python -m federated.server_node --persistent --rounds 10

  Options:
  - --persistent - Keeps server running after rounds complete (for continuous client connections)
  - --rounds - Number of federated learning rounds (default: 10)
  - --min-clients - Minimum clients required (default: 1)

  ---
  2. Start Client Nodes (in separate terminals)

  Terminal 2 - Client 1 (Delhi):
  cd airhub-ml
  python -m federated.client_node --city "Delhi" --country "IN" --persistent

  Terminal 3 - Client 2 (Mumbai):
  cd airhub-ml
  python -m federated.client_node --city "Mumbai" --country "IN" --persistent

  Options:
  - --city / --country - Location for local training data
  - --persistent - Auto-reconnect if server restarts
  - --predict - Request prediction from API instead of training

  ---
  3. Start the API Server

  cd airhub-ml
  python main.py --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8001

  ▎ Note: The frontend expects the API at port 55000 (line 367 in index.html). Update it to 8001 or change the API server port:

  python main.py --port 55000

  ---
  4. Serve the Frontend

  Open frontend/index.html in a browser, or serve it:
  cd frontend
  python -m http.server 3000
  Then visit http://localhost:3000
